Yes — add a config flag and only call Ping when it is enabled.

## 1. Add flag in `application.yml`

```yaml
ping:
  scim:
    enabled: ${PING_SCIM_ENABLED:false}
    base-url: ${PING_SCIM_BASE_URL:}
    bearer-token: ${PING_SCIM_BEARER_TOKEN:}
    username: ${PING_SCIM_USERNAME:}
    password: ${PING_SCIM_PASSWORD:}
    connect-timeout: 5s
    read-timeout: 10s
```

Keep it `false` by default so local/dev does not call Ping unless you explicitly enable it.

## 2. Update `PingScimProperties`

```java
package com.bnpp.pf.partner.repository.ping;

import java.time.Duration;

import org.springframework.boot.context.properties.ConfigurationProperties;

@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "ping.scim")
public record PingScimProperties(
        boolean enabled,
        String baseUrl,
        String bearerToken,
        String username,
        String password,
        Duration connectTimeout,
        Duration readTimeout
) {
}
```

## 3. Use the flag before calling Ping

In the service where you create the user:

```java
@Service
@AllArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class UserService {

    private final UserRepository userRepository;
    private final PingUserClient pingUserClient;
    private final PingScimProperties pingScimProperties;

    @Transactional
    public UserEntity createUser(UserEntity user) {
        UserEntity savedUser = userRepository.save(user);

        if (!pingScimProperties.enabled()) {
            log.info(
                    "Ping SCIM integration is disabled. Skipping Ping create for userId={}",
                    savedUser.getUserId()
            );
            return savedUser;
        }

        try {
            pingUserClient.createUser(savedUser);

            savedUser.setPingSyncStatus("SUCCESS");
            savedUser.setPingLastSyncedAt(Instant.now());
            savedUser.setPingLastError(null);

            return userRepository.save(savedUser);
        } catch (RuntimeException exception) {
            savedUser.setPingSyncStatus("FAILED");
            savedUser.setPingLastError(exception.getMessage());

            userRepository.save(savedUser);

            throw exception;
        }
    }
}
```

