## 4. Your request status may cause a mapper problem

Your payload contains:

```json
"status": "40"
```

But the mapper we discussed accepted values like:

```text
ACTIVE
INACTIVE
DISABLED
DELETED
```

If Ping is eventually called, this code may fail:

```java
mapStatus(user.getStatus())
```

because `"40"` is unsupported.

Map the AS400 status explicitly:

```java
private String mapStatus(Object status) {
    if (status == null) {
        return null;
    }

    String value = status.toString().trim();

    return switch (value) {
        case "40" -> "ACTIVE";
        case "50", "60", "INACTIVE", "DISABLED", "DELETED" -> "INACTIVE";
        case "ACTIVE" -> "ACTIVE";
        default -> throw new IllegalArgumentException(
                "Unsupported user status for Ping: " + value
        );
    };
}
```

Use the real AS400 status mapping agreed by your business team.

